label: anatomy
definition: Study that aims to understand the structure of organisms or their parts.

label: behavioral
definition: Study that induces and/or measures the behavior of the subject.

label: expression
definition: Study that measures or visualizes gene or protein expression within cells or tissues. Focuses on the gene.

label: genomics
definition: Study that measures aspects related to the complete DNA genemone of an organism.

label: cell culture
definition: Study that employs cells isolated from the organism or tissue that are kept alive and studied in vitro.

label: histology
definition: Study that investigates the microscopic structure of tissues.

label: morphology
definition: Study designed to determine the shape and structure of tissues and body parts.

label: cell morphology
definition: Study that specifically seeks to understand the shape and structure of individual cells.

label: transcriptomics
definition: Study that measures RNA transcription in the organism or cell population of interest.

label: electrophysiology
definition: Study that measures electrical impulses within an organism; cell or tissue or the effects of direct electrical stimulation.

label: cell population characterization
definition: Study that measures biochemical; molecular and/or physiological characteristics of populations of cells as opposed to individual cells.

label: radiology
definition: Study that uses at least one of a varity of minimally invasive probes such as x-rays; ultrasound; or nuclear magnetic resonance signals to capture data about the internal structure of intact subjects.

label: microscopy
definition: Study that primarily uses light or electron microscopic imaging.

label: physiology
definition: Study that measures the function or behavior of organs and tissues in living systems.

label: multimodal
definition: Study that employs multiple modalities in signifcant ways.

label: optical
definition: Study that makes measurements using photons in the visible spectrum.

label: cell counting
definition: Study that is designed to quantify cell populations.

label: connectivity
definition: Study that maps or measures functional and/or anatomical connections between nerve cells and their targets or connections between populations of neurons in defined anatomical regions.

label: spatial transcriptomics
definition: Study used to spatially resolve RNA-seq data (and thereby all mRNAs) in individual tissue sections (Wikipedia).

label: expression characterization
definition: Study that charachterizes the cellular; anatomical; or morphological distribution of gene expression. Focuses on population.

label: epigenomics
definition: Study that measures modifications of genetic material that affect transcription but do not alter the organism's DNA.

label: models
definition: Study that creates or charachterizes computational models or simulations of other experimentally observed phenomena.
